NewsBreak offers various ad placements, but you cannot select specific placements yourself. Instead, NewsBreak uses an unlimited native strategy to optimize ad performance by automatically allocating your budget to the placements that achieve your goal CPA (Cost-Per-Action). The available placements include In-feed Ads, In-Article, Related Ads, End of Article, and Immersive Flow. Each placement is designed to integrate naturally within the app or articles for maximum engagement.

Once a campaign is deleted, it cannot be restored or undeleted. If you need to run the campaign again, you'll have to create a new one from scratch. Let me know if you need help with setting up a new campaign!
